V.N., Tyrants Destroyed and Other Stories, 1975





THE SEAPORT


“The Seaport” (Port), written during the first months of 1924, appeared in Rul’ on December 24 of the same year, and now in the current collections. This story was later published, with a handful of minor changes, in Vozvrashchenie Chorba (The Return of Chorb, Slovo, Berlin, 1930), Nabokov’s first collection of short stories, which als